Constructs a new `Weak<T>`, without allocating any memory.
Calling [`upgrade`] on the return value always gives [`None`].

[`upgrade`]: Weak::upgrade

# Examples

```
use std::sync::Weak;

let empty: Weak<i64> = Weak::new();
assert!(empty.upgrade().is_none());
```
